        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic coagulation disorder characterized by a tendency to develop thrombosis resulting from decreased histidine-rich glycoprotein (HRG) plasma levels. Manifestations are variable depending on location of thrombosis but may include headaches diplopia progressive pain limb swelling itching or ulceration and brownish skin discoloration among others."
